id: pm-u5zr
title: "Nightly windows/Node24: package-manifest SDK-surface exemption uses POSIX endsWith — governance-audit runtime.ts check fails on backslash paths"
description: "New nightly red introduced by PR#536 (distinct from pm-b24b init-suite failures on the same leg). tests/unit/packages/package-manifest.spec.ts 'keeps shipped package sources on the public SDK surface' exempts the governance-audit runtime via sourceFile.endsWith(\"governance-audit/runtime.ts\") (spec ~line 862), but sourceFile is built with path.join → on Windows it ends 'governance-audit\\runtime.ts', the exemption never matches, and the file falls into the generic public-SDK-import assertion (expects from \"@unbrained/pm-cli/sdk\", file legitimately imports local ./sdk.ts shim per its resilient-loader design). Spec-side POSIX path assumption class (precedent pm-gf6f); fix = separator-agnostic suffix comparison (compare against path.join(...) or normalize to posix before endsWith). Restoring the windows/Node24 leg to green requires BOTH this and pm-b24b. Consider pinning package-manifest.spec.ts into the windows-regression PR job so spec-side POSIX assumptions are caught pre-merge."
type: Issue
